WEBVTT

00:05.088 --> 00:06.214
Previously, on "Below
Deck Mediterranean"...

00:07.507 --> 00:09.134
I just wanna pay for
anyone but Lexi.

00:09.175 --> 00:10.135
She had bad parents.

00:10.176 --> 00:11.469
No, my parents are amazing.

00:11.511 --> 00:12.554
Your parents
should have aborted you.

00:12.595 --> 00:14.431
-Whoa.
-Oh!

00:14.472 --> 00:16.141
If this wasn't on camera,
I would have smacked your ass.

00:16.182 --> 00:17.684
The real bitch is out now.

00:17.726 --> 00:19.519
I'm gonna tell Sandy
it's either me or her.

00:19.561 --> 00:21.146
-You are replaceable.
-I know.

00:21.187 --> 00:23.648
There's someone sitting
in quarantine right now

00:23.690 --> 00:24.691
to take your job.

00:24.733 --> 00:26.192
The chef I have in quarantine

00:26.234 --> 00:29.070
doesn't have the CV
that Mathew has.

00:29.112 --> 00:31.114
Sometimes it's better to go
with the devil you know

00:31.156 --> 00:32.490
than the devil you don't know.

00:32.532 --> 00:34.367
She said things to me,
she said things to Mat.

00:34.409 --> 00:36.244
She called me a [bleep].

00:36.286 --> 00:38.371
She told me I should have
been aborted multiple times.

00:38.413 --> 00:41.207
Considering how it's permeated
through the entire boat...

00:41.249 --> 00:43.668
-Mm-hmm.
-I have to let you go.

00:43.710 --> 00:45.545
Delaney is still an option.

00:45.587 --> 00:47.589
I think it's best
it's just me and Courtney.

00:47.630 --> 00:49.132
Like, she's on the ball.

00:49.174 --> 00:51.092
I do not want the client
to feel the impact.

00:51.134 --> 00:53.595
Charter number six.
This'll be a shorter charter.

00:53.636 --> 00:55.597
Anthony Evans and Chris Loar.

00:55.638 --> 00:57.557
Anthony is a gospel artist.

00:57.599 --> 00:59.684
And Reyn is lactose-intolerant.

01:02.520 --> 01:04.606
[gasps]
Dave!

01:04.647 --> 01:07.108
Oh, my God.

01:07.150 --> 01:09.569
Injuries... if any guests
or you guys are injured,

01:09.611 --> 01:12.405
I wanna be the first
to know about it.

01:12.447 --> 01:15.742
Hey, Malia, can you come to the
starboard side of the main deck?

01:15.784 --> 01:17.494
Copy.

01:17.535 --> 01:20.747
-Tell me why you're limping.
-I fell.

01:20.789 --> 01:22.582
Why wasn't it reported to me?

01:22.624 --> 01:25.251
-I'm not a chief officer.
-I don't give a [bleep]!

01:25.293 --> 01:27.504
You should have come to me
that he was hurt!

01:27.545 --> 01:29.589
-I didn't know it was that...
-Stop making excuses, Malia!

01:34.928 --> 01:37.472
-The reality is, Malia...
-It's not an excuse!

01:37.514 --> 01:39.391
I asked you to come to me
in the very first meeting,

01:39.432 --> 01:40.684
and you never did.

01:40.725 --> 01:42.560
So from now on,
I don't give a [bleep]

01:42.602 --> 01:46.272
if he hits his head, anything.
It's a liability, period.

01:46.314 --> 01:47.774
Even if it's a bruise,

01:47.816 --> 01:50.485
it's a massive ----ing
bruise, and I just...

01:50.527 --> 01:51.945
-I didn't know it was...
-I don't... I don't trust you.

01:51.986 --> 01:53.279
-...my responsibility.
-I don't trust you.

01:53.321 --> 01:54.280
-Okay.
-I can't trust you.

01:54.322 --> 01:55.532
Okay.

01:58.743 --> 02:00.453
Mm.

02:08.962 --> 02:10.255
Fingerprints, yeah.

02:10.296 --> 02:11.673
And then we'll get changed.

02:14.009 --> 02:15.927
So, you need to go make
an incident report...

02:17.512 --> 02:18.680
Sure.

02:21.349 --> 02:22.434
No.

02:24.436 --> 02:25.979
I might do a cruditÃ©
meat and cheese,

02:26.021 --> 02:26.980
and skip the fruit plate.

02:27.022 --> 02:28.523
Yeah, no one really touches it.

02:28.565 --> 02:30.817
All right, is this gonna
be an early morning,

02:30.859 --> 02:32.318
early night type of crowd?

02:32.360 --> 02:34.362
I hope it's not a
late, late night,

02:34.404 --> 02:36.573
because I've only got
two stews, you know?

02:36.614 --> 02:38.283
You know what I'm saying?

02:38.324 --> 02:40.952
Before Lady Michelle,
I had seven girls under me.

02:40.994 --> 02:43.329
Now I've got one.

02:43.371 --> 02:45.206
We've just gotta
keep pushin' through.

02:45.248 --> 02:47.334
I'm not disregarding
my gut ever again,

02:47.375 --> 02:49.544
and if this blows up in my face,

02:49.586 --> 02:51.629
then that's on me, and I will
take responsibility for that.

02:55.800 --> 02:57.594
What was it about?

02:57.635 --> 03:00.555
An incident...
like, David's leg.

03:02.974 --> 03:04.309
[bleep]

03:04.351 --> 03:06.227
It happened not
during work hours,

03:06.269 --> 03:07.562
not in a work-related incident.

03:07.604 --> 03:09.356
Yeah.

03:09.397 --> 03:11.399
If he needed to report it,
he should have done it himself.

03:11.441 --> 03:13.651
Deck team cuddle, come on.

03:13.693 --> 03:15.570
Oh, I'm slightly wet, I'm sorry.

03:18.740 --> 03:20.533
-Hey, bro.
-Hey, buddy.

03:20.575 --> 03:21.659
What's going on?

03:21.701 --> 03:23.453
What's the vibe on deck today?

03:23.495 --> 03:25.580
-A bit limpy.
-Limpy Dave?

03:25.622 --> 03:27.374
Yeah, it's all good.

03:27.415 --> 03:29.250
So, can you say a little
prayer that everyone

03:29.292 --> 03:31.336
-likes everything tonight, man?
-They're going to.

03:31.378 --> 03:33.254
Well, we've got a religious
group coming on board,

03:33.296 --> 03:35.507
so we should probably get
with the prayers now.

03:35.548 --> 03:37.467
I feel very lucky I'm here.

03:37.509 --> 03:39.719
I feel like I've escaped
being fired many times.

03:39.761 --> 03:41.888
I'm like Mat the cat...
nine lives.

03:41.930 --> 03:43.306
Think back to the last
five charters...

03:43.348 --> 03:44.849
Yeah?

03:44.891 --> 03:46.017
Where they've loved everything
you've done.

03:46.059 --> 03:47.268
-Yeah.
-It's gonna be fine.

03:47.310 --> 03:48.436
-Yeah?
-Yeah, of course.

03:50.605 --> 03:52.941
<i>Malia, Malia,</i>
<i>please come to the bridge.</i>

03:52.982 --> 03:55.902
Copy.
Ugh.

03:55.944 --> 03:58.571
I don't know the severity
of his injury.

03:58.613 --> 04:01.783
David may feel okay,
but God forbid

04:01.825 --> 04:03.952
in two weeks something happens,
he passes a blood clot.

04:03.993 --> 04:07.038
He has not reported the injury,
so guess who's liable?

04:07.080 --> 04:09.833
The owner.
The vessel. And me.

04:09.874 --> 04:13.461
We're two stewardesses!

04:13.503 --> 04:15.964
I've got a headache, [bleep].

04:16.006 --> 04:17.674
What would be your most
pointless super power?

04:17.716 --> 04:19.426
-Fly.
-Fly?

04:19.467 --> 04:20.677
Yeah, it's...
it's always gonna be flying.

04:20.719 --> 04:22.554
-What about you?
-To read people's minds.

04:22.595 --> 04:24.389
So, I would like
to speak to animals.

04:24.431 --> 04:26.474
But then what if
I found out that animals

04:26.516 --> 04:28.059
are actually thick as sh--,
and I've wasted my power,

04:28.101 --> 04:29.561
and like, all they
just do is, like,

04:29.602 --> 04:31.521
actually they just go, "Meh."

04:31.563 --> 04:33.648
Like, that's actually
what they're saying.

04:33.690 --> 04:36.568
Everyone on this boat has
created such a great environment

04:36.609 --> 04:39.779
for me to be able to share
my thoughts and feelings.

04:39.821 --> 04:42.073
So, it's worrying,
thinking that I'm leaving that

04:42.115 --> 04:44.451
and then maybe having to deal
with other people's

04:44.492 --> 04:47.871
impressions of me
and my lifestyle.

04:47.912 --> 04:49.622
I'm trying to work
out the next job.

04:49.664 --> 04:51.458
I just messaged
my old chief officer.

04:51.499 --> 04:52.792
I'll say, "Oh, do you need
someone to work for the winter."

04:52.834 --> 04:54.544
I'll give him a recommendation.

04:54.586 --> 04:57.464
-I'm...
-Yeah.

04:57.505 --> 04:59.382
-Yeah, lovely.
-Yeah, yeah, yeah.

05:00.717 --> 05:02.969
So, Malia,
I'm obviously upset.

05:03.011 --> 05:05.138
I made it very clear, day one,

05:05.180 --> 05:07.682
if anyone gets injured,
I don't care...

05:07.724 --> 05:10.935
fingers, head, whatever it is,
it's reported.

05:10.977 --> 05:12.479
If David had been working,
slipped and fell...

05:12.520 --> 05:13.688
Yeah.

05:13.730 --> 05:15.023
While working and got
that bruise,

05:15.065 --> 05:16.691
I would have filled out
an incident report.

05:16.733 --> 05:19.652
When the incident happened,
it was after-hours.

05:19.694 --> 05:21.154
You report at work...

05:21.196 --> 05:22.572
Okay, I see where
you're going technically.

05:22.614 --> 05:23.823
-Yeah.
-But here's the deal...

05:23.865 --> 05:25.408
-He's limping.
-And he should...

05:25.450 --> 05:26.743
I get what you're saying,
it could become

05:26.785 --> 05:28.536
-something more serious.
-Yeah.

05:28.578 --> 05:29.537
I'm sorry that that didn't
get communicated to you.

05:29.579 --> 05:31.039
Thank you.

05:31.081 --> 05:32.874
The captain has the right
to know what's going on

05:32.916 --> 05:34.542
with their crew at all times,

05:34.584 --> 05:36.503
especially when
it comes to injuries.

05:36.544 --> 05:39.005
David should have reported it,
I should have reminded him.

05:39.047 --> 05:41.007
At the end of the day,
that's my fault.

05:41.049 --> 05:43.468
-And I'm sorry I yelled at you.
-That's okay.

05:43.510 --> 05:45.053
-Because I have the highest...
-I just, like...

05:45.095 --> 05:48.682
You are... like, for me,
I trust you 1,000 percent.

05:48.723 --> 05:50.600
And when I found out...

05:50.642 --> 05:52.394
Yeah, that really hurt, for
you to say you don't trust me.

05:52.435 --> 05:54.688
-Yeah, I know, I trust you.
-That hurt me to the core.

05:54.729 --> 05:56.064
That's fair. I get it.
I'm sorry.

05:56.106 --> 05:58.566
I'm sorry.
I'll make sure it happens.

05:58.608 --> 06:00.402
Okay. Thanks, Malia.

06:06.491 --> 06:07.867
[yawns]

06:07.909 --> 06:09.160
Hi, this is Sandy.

06:11.037 --> 06:12.080
Hi!

06:20.130 --> 06:22.048
Oh, okay.
Okay, got it.

06:22.090 --> 06:23.842
All right, well,
thank you for the heads up.

06:23.883 --> 06:24.926
-All right, bye-bye.
-Bye-bye!

06:26.761 --> 06:28.138
...but now I'm
gonna have to redo it.

06:28.179 --> 06:30.181
Think you're gonna be
out for the count.

06:30.223 --> 06:33.768
It's gonna be Mzi mornings,
Dave lates.

06:33.810 --> 06:36.146
So, I'm gonna put Dave
kind of at the night shift,

06:36.187 --> 06:38.898
where he won't be doing
as much physical labor.

06:38.940 --> 06:41.067
As long as you can
stand and wash dishes...

06:41.109 --> 06:43.153
I can certainly do that.

06:43.194 --> 06:45.488
Lloyd and Mzi will
now just kinda have

06:45.530 --> 06:47.115
to step up their game
during the day.

06:47.157 --> 06:48.950
Hopefully Captain Sandy
can see

06:48.992 --> 06:51.036
I'm trying to remedy
the situation.

06:52.787 --> 06:55.248
All crew, all crew,
please get into your whites

06:55.290 --> 06:57.625
and let's meet on the
dock in five minutes.

06:59.127 --> 07:01.755
And just so you know,
we have three charter guests

07:01.796 --> 07:04.591
that are gonna be late because
of their COVID test is late.

07:04.632 --> 07:05.800
Okay.

07:08.845 --> 07:12.182
Oh, can you get me a couple
of the orchid flowers?

07:12.223 --> 07:13.725
-Are they downstairs?
-No, they're right here.

07:13.767 --> 07:14.768
Plates...

07:17.103 --> 07:19.272
Charter number six.

07:19.314 --> 07:22.108
Pull cutlery,
plates, placemats...

07:22.150 --> 07:23.485
-Yeah.
-Napkins.

07:23.526 --> 07:24.486
Okay, are we doing
welcome snacks?

07:24.527 --> 07:25.612
Yeah.

07:25.653 --> 07:26.780
Yeah, he's got some ready, so...

07:26.821 --> 07:27.822
I just need, like,
three minutes.

07:27.864 --> 07:29.783
-Whew!
-Let's go!

07:29.824 --> 07:30.992
-Hey, hey!
-Hi!

07:31.034 --> 07:32.786
Hey! I'm Anthony.
Good to see you.

07:32.827 --> 07:34.287
-Captain, nice to meet you.
-Hi, welcome.

07:34.329 --> 07:36.623
-Hi, Anthony, sorry.
-Katie.

07:36.664 --> 07:37.749
-Hi, I'm Mat.
-Hey, Mat.

07:37.791 --> 07:39.084
Katie, nice to meet you, Reyn.

07:39.125 --> 07:40.794
Anthony, good to
meet you, David.

07:40.835 --> 07:42.962
-So nice to have you.
-Thank you.

07:43.004 --> 07:44.631
So, Katie's gonna show
you around the vessel.

07:44.673 --> 07:45.840
So, just head onto the boat.

07:45.882 --> 07:47.008
Sounds great.

07:49.761 --> 07:51.304
Thank you.

07:51.346 --> 07:52.931
Okay, great.

07:52.972 --> 07:54.265
Should we do a tour of the boat?

07:54.307 --> 07:56.768
Thank you.

07:56.810 --> 07:58.061
This is our sundeck.

07:58.103 --> 08:01.147
We have a big-ass
Jacuzzi right here.

08:01.189 --> 08:03.024
It's awesome.

08:08.029 --> 08:09.698
Lloyd, no Christmas songs.

08:10.699 --> 08:11.700
This is the sundeck aft.

08:11.741 --> 08:13.243
Ooh, I love this.

08:16.246 --> 08:17.330
Why?

08:17.372 --> 08:18.957
There's so much pressure now.

08:18.998 --> 08:20.000
I can't remember what
she just asked me to do.

08:20.041 --> 08:22.002
Good start.

08:22.043 --> 08:24.754
As a stewardess, the smallest
boat I worked on before this

08:24.796 --> 08:27.132
