there was five of us.

08:27.173 --> 08:29.676
I can't believe that we're about
to do this trip with two stews.

08:29.718 --> 08:32.053
Like, anxiety is real.

08:32.095 --> 08:34.556
Okay, comin' in.

08:34.597 --> 08:36.349
Then we come through
to the primary cabin.

08:36.391 --> 08:38.727
Ooh!
Beautiful.

08:40.603 --> 08:42.564
So in here, we've got
his and hers bathrooms.

08:42.605 --> 08:43.606
Cheers.

08:45.233 --> 08:46.860
-Are you ready?
-Yep.

08:46.901 --> 08:48.153
-You're gonna be on the bow.
-By myself?

08:48.194 --> 08:49.195
All you're doing
is pulling the lines in.

08:49.237 --> 08:50.864
Yeah.

08:50.905 --> 08:52.240
They're gonna undo it,
pull, pull, pull.

08:55.994 --> 08:58.038
I do feel now that
I can actually do that

08:58.079 --> 09:01.124
by myself without having
somebody watching me.

09:02.292 --> 09:05.128
Yeah.
Yeah.

09:05.170 --> 09:08.590
So, port will come in
first, then starboard.

09:08.631 --> 09:09.632
You got it.

09:11.426 --> 09:14.596
I should have waited on y'all.
My impatient self.

09:14.637 --> 09:16.306
Can I get you anything
to drink at all?

09:16.348 --> 09:18.016
I have a childish thing
about me.

09:18.058 --> 09:20.060
I like Sprite with grenadine...

09:20.101 --> 09:21.644
it's a Shirley Temple, but I
just say Sprite with grenadine.

09:21.686 --> 09:23.063
-Sure.
-It makes... you know.

09:23.104 --> 09:24.898
-It makes you feel adult.
-Cool... yeah, yeah.

09:24.939 --> 09:26.149
He doesn't drink, and hey,
if that's what he wants,

09:26.191 --> 09:27.692
that's what he'll get.

09:27.734 --> 09:29.235
I'll grab you some
plates and stuff,

09:29.277 --> 09:30.904
-and then I'll go grab you that.
-Thank you.

09:30.945 --> 09:32.906
It's just exactly
what we needed right now,

09:32.947 --> 09:34.616
especially for me and Courtney.

09:34.657 --> 09:36.910
Mzi, you could just let
go of the port one first.

09:36.951 --> 09:37.952
<i>Copy that.</i>

09:39.954 --> 09:40.955
<i>Port bow line coming in first.</i>

09:42.791 --> 09:44.668
<i>Malia, you can</i>
<i>free up the lines.</i>

09:44.709 --> 09:46.836
Copy, freeing up
the stern lines.

09:46.878 --> 09:49.172
All right, Dave, yours first.

09:49.214 --> 09:50.924
<i>Port bow line is on board.</i>

09:50.965 --> 09:53.635
That is all stern lines on
board, all stern lines on board.

09:55.970 --> 09:57.889
Whoa, what's going on there?

09:57.931 --> 10:00.350
Captain Sandy, you're close
to the port side dolphin.

10:00.392 --> 10:03.770
Yeah, pretty freaky.

10:03.812 --> 10:05.980
Captain Sandy, you're very
close to the dolphin.

10:06.022 --> 10:07.440
-[bleep]
-Get a fender ready.

10:07.482 --> 10:09.651
Oh, God!

10:09.693 --> 10:11.319
[bleep]

10:11.361 --> 10:13.279
-Coming up...
-I'm freaking out.

10:13.321 --> 10:14.823
Can you just say
a little prayer

10:14.864 --> 10:16.157
that they love
everything tonight?

10:16.199 --> 10:17.951
I'm not a ----ing mother.

10:24.082 --> 10:25.458
Whoa... Captain Sandy, you're
very close to the dolphin.

10:26.918 --> 10:28.461
-[bleep]
-Get a fender ready.

10:28.503 --> 10:30.463
Oh, God!

10:31.923 --> 10:33.258
Lady Michelle's
a very heavy vessel.

10:33.299 --> 10:36.052
When you have 909 gross tons
in the water

10:36.094 --> 10:37.345
with two different currents,

10:37.387 --> 10:39.514
and the wind matching one
of the currents,

10:39.556 --> 10:42.183
it's very difficult
to get out of that hole.

10:42.225 --> 10:44.019
And I overcorrect to starboard,

10:44.060 --> 10:48.189
I need to bring it back to port,
so it pushes the stern over.

10:48.231 --> 10:50.358
So now, as I come out,

10:50.400 --> 10:54.237
I'm overcorrecting, my stern
could hit that port dolphin.

10:54.279 --> 10:56.740
-Ooh.
-Whew.

10:56.781 --> 10:58.867
<i>Clearing both dolphins</i>
<i>off your stern.</i>

10:58.908 --> 11:00.118
So sweet.

11:00.160 --> 11:01.870
Filtered water for the rice.

11:01.911 --> 11:04.456
Clear of all traffic, all clear.

11:04.497 --> 11:05.874
Thank you very much.

11:05.915 --> 11:06.875
Insane.

11:06.916 --> 11:08.293
This could be heaven.

11:08.335 --> 11:09.961
Nicely done, guys.

11:10.003 --> 11:12.130
-Nice work, Mzi.
-Thank you.

11:12.172 --> 11:13.381
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

11:13.423 --> 11:15.050
Ow!

11:15.091 --> 11:16.968
Can I get you gentlemen
another drink?

11:17.010 --> 11:19.054
-I'll do gin and tonic.
-Tequila soda.

11:19.095 --> 11:20.889
-Perfect.
-You're, like, the queen?

11:20.930 --> 11:22.891
-The queen?
-Of the...

11:22.932 --> 11:23.892
-Of interior.
-Yeah, yeah, yeah.

11:23.933 --> 11:25.310
I'll take it!

11:29.481 --> 11:31.024
Deck crew, deck crew, Katie.

11:31.066 --> 11:32.400
Can you please clean
the crew mess?

11:32.442 --> 11:34.527
<i>Copy.</i>
<i>David, help interior.</i>

11:34.569 --> 11:35.779
Copy.

11:35.820 --> 11:38.406
-...and tequila.
-Thank you.

11:42.285 --> 11:43.453
Okay.

11:43.495 --> 11:45.997
I'm going to get changed.

11:46.039 --> 11:47.916
You have to help me just
move this over onto that.

11:47.957 --> 11:49.834
-Shirley Temples?
-Shirley Temples.

11:49.876 --> 11:51.169
Shirley Temples.

11:51.211 --> 11:52.253
We go to restaurants and
we order like children,

11:52.295 --> 11:53.505
everybody gets a Shirley Temple.

11:53.546 --> 11:54.964
Hey, if it tastes good.

11:56.966 --> 11:58.301
Hey, hey.

11:58.343 --> 11:59.844
So, do you wanna turn
laundry and sh--...

11:59.886 --> 12:02.055
-Yeah.
-And I'll just holler at you.

12:06.476 --> 12:08.978
Here's our deck schedule
for this charter.

