37:56.026 --> 37:58.028
Yeah, my back can't take it.

38:07.704 --> 38:09.831
-Morning!
-Hey, good morning.

38:09.873 --> 38:10.874
How are you?

38:14.794 --> 38:16.296
[bleep]

38:19.716 --> 38:21.009
Yeah.

38:21.051 --> 38:22.844
I completely forgot
about the paddleboards.

38:22.886 --> 38:24.804
There's a lot of responsibility
on the morning shift.

38:24.846 --> 38:27.599
It's just frustrating, because
I know that I can do better.

38:27.640 --> 38:29.809
Why waste time in the gym when
you could be on a paddleboard?

38:30.894 --> 38:32.020
-Enjoy it!
-Appreciate it.

38:32.062 --> 38:33.730
-Good morning.
-Morning.

38:35.357 --> 38:36.691
Yeah.

38:36.733 --> 38:37.984
-So, this morning?
-Mm-hmm?

38:41.196 --> 38:43.198
At 7:30.

38:43.239 --> 38:44.699
So, who's your early
morning guy?

38:44.741 --> 38:46.117
Mzi.

38:46.159 --> 38:47.160
Ah.

38:48.286 --> 38:49.913
Thank you.

38:56.753 --> 38:58.254
Let me get you a paddle.

38:58.296 --> 39:00.048
Oh, I'm just sitting on
her board, like a dog.

39:00.090 --> 39:01.049
-You're just gonna sit on it?
-Yeah.

39:01.091 --> 39:02.717
-Ah.
-How are you?

39:02.759 --> 39:04.052
Working hard.

39:04.094 --> 39:05.887
We thought Lechelle went
out on the paddleboard;

39:05.929 --> 39:06.971
now the other lady's with her.

39:07.013 --> 39:09.349
[bleep] yeah, drop-off day.

39:09.391 --> 39:10.892
[bleep] yeah.

39:10.934 --> 39:12.936
Um, quick note about mornings.

39:12.977 --> 39:14.938
The paddleboards
should actually be out.

39:14.979 --> 39:16.106
-Out.
-Yeah.

39:16.147 --> 39:17.941
-Sorry.
-Oh, you're up early?

39:17.982 --> 39:20.068
How did you sleep?

39:20.110 --> 39:21.820
Amazing!

39:21.861 --> 39:23.321
Hello, Mathew.

39:23.363 --> 39:25.073
-All's well.
-Okay, bye.

39:25.115 --> 39:26.199
Bye.

39:31.287 --> 39:33.707
-How did everyone sleep?
-Thank you so much.

39:40.296 --> 39:42.048
Leaving such
a supportive bubble,

39:42.090 --> 39:44.342
I'm concerned what's gonna
happen after the season

39:44.384 --> 39:47.762
and being able to go forward
and have to deal

39:47.804 --> 39:50.390
with trying to get that level
of acceptance from new people.

39:55.812 --> 39:57.897
-Banana bread.
-Wow.

39:57.939 --> 39:59.399
If anyone wants a last
water sports sesh,

39:59.441 --> 40:01.651
we do have to be
anchors up shortly.

40:01.693 --> 40:03.278
-Okay, we're good.
-Nice.

40:03.319 --> 40:04.738
Katie?

40:04.779 --> 40:06.448
So, herreros rancheros,
chipotle...

40:06.489 --> 40:07.657
Chipotle salsa.

40:10.785 --> 40:12.203
Oh, my gosh, wow.

40:14.789 --> 40:17.834
Oh, yes, this is
my kinda thing.

40:17.876 --> 40:21.004
Katie?
What's the vibe?

40:21.046 --> 40:22.380
I just wanna know
if they hate me.

40:22.422 --> 40:24.215
They ----ing love you,
I swear to God.

40:24.257 --> 40:26.134
I will hate you in a minute.

40:26.176 --> 40:27.469
Don't.

40:27.510 --> 40:32.057
I feel insecure
when I get any criticism.

40:32.098 --> 40:35.143
All I can hear is I ----ed up,
and that's not healthy.

40:35.185 --> 40:36.978
-All right!
-Do you need a hand?

40:37.020 --> 40:38.480
-The duo is back!
-The duo!

40:38.521 --> 40:42.317
All crew, all crew,
ETA to the anchor is 16 minutes.

40:42.359 --> 40:44.027
Copy that.

40:45.987 --> 40:47.197
-Coming up.
-Coming up.

40:49.991 --> 40:51.326
-Lloyd?
-Yeah.

40:51.368 --> 40:52.494
You wanna run forward and
prep the anchors?

40:52.535 --> 40:53.703
Yeah.

40:53.745 --> 40:55.163
Coming up on the transom.

40:55.205 --> 40:57.207
Mzi, run forward
for anchors, please.

40:58.792 --> 41:00.835
Bridge, bridge, that
is the transom closed

41:00.877 --> 41:02.504
and us ready to haul the anchor.

41:02.545 --> 41:05.340
<i>Terrific, you can start</i>
<i>hauling anchor</i>

41:05.382 --> 41:06.841
<i>as soon as you're up there.</i>

41:06.883 --> 41:07.967
I love this.

41:11.054 --> 41:12.305
She just said you can
haul the anchor.

41:12.347 --> 41:13.807
Oh, sorry.

41:17.769 --> 41:20.063
Anchor is at the water line,
at the water line.

41:21.856 --> 41:23.733
Anchor is home, anchor is home.

41:29.781 --> 41:31.032
I'm gonna go pack and change.

41:31.074 --> 41:32.409
I'm gonna go watch
them back it in.

41:32.450 --> 41:35.370
What the [bleep]?

41:35.412 --> 41:37.455
The fender's in the wrong spot.

41:37.497 --> 41:40.333
Please take the
anchor ball down,

41:40.375 --> 41:42.210
please take
the anchor ball down.

41:42.252 --> 41:43.503
[bleep]'s sake!

41:43.545 --> 41:44.963
Ugh!

41:45.005 --> 41:46.881
-Copy.
-We don't look like pros.

41:46.923 --> 41:48.091
Ugh!

41:48.133 --> 41:49.884
I think people are
getting tired,

41:49.926 --> 41:53.013
and they're not doing a
thorough check of their work,

41:53.054 --> 41:55.390
and I'm not gonna let it fly.

41:55.432 --> 41:57.058
What up?

41:57.100 --> 41:58.768
Happy epaulette Friday
to you, sir.

41:58.810 --> 42:01.021
<i>Nine minutes till</i>
<i>we get to the marina.</i>

42:01.062 --> 42:02.147
Copy, understood.

42:02.188 --> 42:03.523
You have four minutes.

42:03.565 --> 42:05.150
Change into your epaulettes.

42:05.191 --> 42:06.276
How's it going?

42:06.317 --> 42:07.569
Yeah, it's gonna be a new...

42:07.610 --> 42:10.196
David, get out on deck,
please, now.

42:10.238 --> 42:11.948
Heaving lines, set up, please.

42:14.451 --> 42:16.077
Let's go.

42:16.119 --> 42:18.246
<i>Six minutes till we</i>
<i>get to the marina.</i>

42:18.288 --> 42:20.123
[bleep]'s sake.

42:22.208 --> 42:24.085
Mzi, Mzi, Lloyd.

42:24.127 --> 42:25.378
I think he's getting his whites
on, he might be off the comms.

42:27.172 --> 42:29.257
Malia, I'm moving to
the starboard wing station,

42:29.299 --> 42:31.426
so let me know when your dock
guys are on the stern.

42:31.468 --> 42:32.927
Yep, copy that.

42:32.969 --> 42:34.512
Dave, Dave, or Malia, can

42:34.554 --> 42:36.473
I get some help getting
this fender to its holder?

42:36.514 --> 42:38.099
On my way, Lloyd.

42:38.141 --> 42:40.935
That's awesome.

42:40.977 --> 42:42.228
You're gonna be on the bow,
if that's okay.

42:42.270 --> 42:43.271
-Yeah.
<i>-Two minutes.</i>

42:43.313 --> 42:44.439
All right, good to drop.

42:44.481 --> 42:47.275
-Yeah.
-Fenders over!

42:47.317 --> 42:49.569
Lloyd, Lloyd, port bow line,
port bow line.

42:49.611 --> 42:51.571
Fifteen feet and closing
to the vessel astern.

42:51.613 --> 42:52.989
We need to walk to port.

42:53.031 --> 42:55.450
Well, everybody else
is backed in.

42:55.492 --> 42:56.576
No pressure.

42:56.618 --> 42:58.161
Throwing stern lines.

43:00.663 --> 43:02.916
Port to spring going across now.

43:04.000 --> 43:05.543
<i>Port bow line on.</i>

43:05.585 --> 43:08.254
<i>Five feet off the dock, getting</i>
<i>stern lines across now.</i>

43:09.381 --> 43:10.340
-Come on, Mzi.
-Ah!

43:10.382 --> 43:12.384
Quick!

43:12.425 --> 43:14.469
Ugh.

43:14.511 --> 43:16.388
Okay, we can put this one on,
we can put this one on.

43:16.429 --> 43:18.098
Bump ahead.

43:18.139 --> 43:20.600
The port dolphin is right
in front of me, I can't.

43:20.642 --> 43:22.560
We're in their ground line.

43:22.602 --> 43:25.105
We're about to hit some ground
lines, and it's my fault.

43:27.065 --> 43:28.191
[bleep]'s sake!

43:28.233 --> 43:30.360
Next, on "Below Deck Med"...

43:30.402 --> 43:32.153
This is my favorite night out,

43:32.195 --> 43:33.405
I think because
Lexi wasn't here.

43:33.446 --> 43:35.031
Oh sh--, here we go.

43:40.537 --> 43:43.915
It really, really
gets under my skin

43:43.957 --> 43:45.875
when we start making
rookie-rookie mistakes.

43:45.917 --> 43:48.586
If you see me hustling,
I expect to see you hustling.

43:48.628 --> 43:51.089
My stomach's so sore,
I don't get it.

43:51.131 --> 43:53.383
I just feel sick.
Maybe it's, like, nerves.

43:53.425 --> 43:54.884
Everyone's very anxious.

43:54.926 --> 43:58.179
Lloyd, slow down.

43:58.221 --> 43:59.180
You can't even tell the colors.

43:59.222 --> 44:00.515
Something is off with Lloyd.

44:00.557 --> 44:02.225
[vomiting]

44:02.267 --> 44:04.060
I'm sending Lloyd ashore
because his blood pressure

44:04.102 --> 44:06.354
is really high,
he has chest pains.

44:06.396 --> 44:07.522
Wait, what happened to Lloyd?

44:07.564 --> 44:10.233
-What happened?
-It's serious.
